.TH CURLENT 1 "December 2025" "curlent" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
curlent \- wget-like command-line torrent downloader
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B curlent
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fITORRENT\fR|\fIMAGNET\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B curlent
is a simple command-line torrent downloader using libtorrent.
It downloads from .torrent files or magnet links and displays a colored progress bar with speed and ETA.
After download completes, it seeds to a target ratio (default 2.0).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " " \fIDIR\fR
Output directory (default: current directory)
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-interface " " \fIIF\fR
Bind to network interface with kill switch.
If the interface goes down, curlent immediately exits to prevent IP leaks.
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-ratio " " \fIRATIO\fR
Seed ratio target (default: 2.0)
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-no\-seed
Exit immediately after download, don't seed
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Minimal output
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message and exit
.SH CONFIGURATION
Settings can be persisted in \fI~/.config/curlent/config\fR:
.PP
.nf
# Output directory
output = ~/Downloads

# Bind to network interface with kill switch
interface = wg0

# Seed ratio target
ratio = 1.5

# Exit after download, don't seed
no-seed = false

# Quiet mode
quiet = false
.fi
.PP
Command line options override config file settings.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/curlent/config
Configuration file
.TP
.I ~/.cache/curlent/session_state
DHT session state for faster startup
.SH EXAMPLES
Download from .torrent file:
.PP
.nf
curlent ubuntu.torrent
.fi
.PP
Download from magnet link (must be quoted):
.PP
.nf
curlent "magnet:?xt=urn:btih:..."
.fi
.PP
Bind to VPN interface with kill switch:
.PP
.nf
curlent -i tun0 ubuntu.torrent
.fi
.PP
Download only, don't seed:
.PP
.nf
curlent -n ubuntu.torrent
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
Error or kill switch triggered
